      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 55: 🔴 Critical Issues - This authorization path trusts `cert-\u003egetLongId()` as the device id but does not validate that the device belongs to `cert-\u003eissuer` before accepting the channel. Because `Conversation::isPeerAuthorized()` explicitly assumes the device has already been confirmed, callers handling untrusted requests must enforce that precondition here or in `ConversationModule::isPeerAuthorized()`. Suggested fix: move the confirmed-device check into `ConversationModule::isPeerAuthorized()` so all channel handlers get the same protection.\n```suggestion\nreturn convModule-\u003eisPeerAuthorized(conversationId, issuerUri, deviceId, true);\n```",
      "revId": "84f79fbfe5b0360fb1806b53fee1fd5a5b0f69a4",
