      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2806: 🔴 Critical Issues - `isPeerAuthorized()` only verifies that `uri` is a member and `deviceId` is not banned; it never verifies that `deviceId` is actually a trusted/confirmed device belonging to `uri`. The new callers are channel admission paths, so the header assumption in `Conversation::isPeerAuthorized()` is not enforced at the boundary. A certificate/device that is not present in the conversation devices list could be authorized as long as it claims a member issuer and is not explicitly banned. Please add an explicit member-device binding/known-device check before returning true. For example:\n```suggestion\nif (conv-\u003econversation) {\n    const auto authorized \u003d conv-\u003econversation-\u003eisPeerAuthorized(uri, deviceId, includeInvited);\n    return authorized \u0026\u0026 conv-\u003econversation-\u003ehasDeviceForMember(uri, deviceId);\n}\n```",
      "revId": "84f79fbfe5b0360fb1806b53fee1fd5a5b0f69a4",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
